01:29.589 --> 01:31.258 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

01:31.291 --> 01:33.193 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LINDSEY GRAHAM (R), South
Carolina: Had you
ever met President Trump
personally?

01:33.226 --> 01:36.263 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NEIL GORSUCH, Supreme Court
Nominee: Not until
my interview.

01:36.296 --> 01:37.931 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

01:37.965 --> 01:40.968 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LINDSEY GRAHAM: In that
interview, did he
ever ask you to overrule Roe v.
Wade?

01:41.001 --> 01:41.969 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
NEIL GORSUCH: No, Senator.

01:42.002 --> 01:43.236 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

01:43.270 --> 01:44.504 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LINDSEY GRAHAM: What would you
have done if
he had asked?

01:44.538 --> 01:50.911 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NEIL GORSUCH: Senator, I would
have walked
out the door.

01:50.944 --> 01:53.080 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's not what judges do.

01:53.113 --> 01:57.217 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They don't do it at that end of
Pennsylvania
Avenue, and they shouldn't do it
at this end

01:57.250 --> 01:59.086 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
either, respectfully.

01:59.119 --> 02:03.624 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We will have
extensive excerpts
from and analysis of today's
hearing in just

02:03.657 --> 02:05.459 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
a moment.

02:05.492 --> 02:09.696 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, first, the other big story
of this day,
a full-court press by the
president and the

02:09.730 --> 02:14.634 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
speaker of the House, Paul Ryan,
to pass a
new health care bill that aims
to replace

02:14.668 --> 02:20.007 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
major components of the current
law, the Affordable
Care Act, known as Obamacare.

02:20.040 --> 02:25.879 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Time is ticking before a crucial
vote in the
House on Thursday, and
Republicans know there

02:25.912 --> 02:29.349 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
may not be any Democrats who
will support
it then.

02:29.383 --> 02:32.419 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Our Lisa Desjardins reports from
Capitol Hill.

02:32.452 --> 02:36.256 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Witness the art
of trying
to close the deal.

02:36.289 --> 02:37.758 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
QUESTION: Do you have the votes,
Mr. President?

02:37.791 --> 02:39.926 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
Think so.

02:39.960 --> 02:44.464 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: President Trump
at the Capitol
pushing for votes on the GOP
health care bill,

02:44.498 --> 02:50.370 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
telling members privately their
jobs are at
risk if they don't pass a repeal
bill.

02:50.404 --> 02:53.206 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
White House spokesman Sean
Spicer summed up
the argument later.

02:53.240 --> 02:55.342 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEAN SPICER, White House Press
Secretary:
Yes, I think there's going to be
a price to

02:55.375 --> 02:57.744 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
be paid, and it's going to be
with their own
voters.

02:57.778 --> 03:03.150 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And they're going to have go
back and explain
to them why they made a
commitment to them

03:03.183 --> 03:05.018 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and then didn't follow through.

03:05.052 --> 03:08.255 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: As the White
House pushes,
GOP leaders at the Capitol are
sounding more

03:08.288 --> 03:09.256 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
enthusiastic.

03:09.289 --> 03:10.924 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

03:10.957 --> 03:12.459 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL RYAN (R-WI), Speaker of the
House: I
just got to say, editorial, the
president

03:12.492 --> 03:14.294 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
just came here and knocked the
ball out of
the park.

03:14.327 --> 03:16.063 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He knocked the cover off the
ball.

03:16.096 --> 03:19.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It is a big moment, and I think
our members
are beginning to appreciate just
what kind

03:19.466 --> 03:21.334 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of rendezvous with destiny we
have right here.

03:21.368 --> 03:23.937 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But destiny
requires votes.

03:23.970 --> 03:28.341 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To win them, Speaker Ryan and
his team did
more than invite a president;
they changed

03:28.375 --> 03:36.249 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
their bill, adding 21 pages of
policy amendments
last night geared to win key
groups, for conservatives,

03:36.283 --> 03:41.288 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
some Medicaid changes, like
letting states
add a work requirement for the
program and

03:41.321 --> 03:46.259 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
giving states the option of a
block grant
Medicaid payment that would
likely cut the

03:46.293 --> 03:48.095 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
program.

03:48.128 --> 03:53.166 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Finally, a new limit from
Republicans: No
new states could join the
Medicaid expansion.

03:53.200 --> 03:57.170 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Add to that, again, for
conservatives, faster
tax cuts.

03:57.204 --> 04:03.643 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This new version would repeal of
all Obamacare
taxes immediately, instead of
next year.

04:03.677 --> 04:08.448 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But those changes didn't go far
enough for
some in the conservative Freedom
Caucus, like

04:08.482 --> 04:09.449 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Ohio's Jim Jordan.

04:09.483 --> 04:10.450 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
QUESTION: Congratulations on
the...

04:10.484 --> 04:11.685 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

04:11.718 --> 04:13.220 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JIM JORDAN (R), Ohio: Oh, it
wasn't as good
as we hoped.

04:13.253 --> 04:17.624 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: He is still a
hard no, as
the Freedom Caucus seems split.

04:17.657 --> 04:22.362 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is why last night's changes
also offer
something to a different group:
moderates.

04:22.395 --> 04:28.835 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For them, Republicans added
roughly $85 billion
in tax deductions for health
care, with the

04:28.869 --> 04:33.406 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
idea that the Senate will target
that money
more to seniors.

04:33.440 --> 04:37.210 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As a result, Representative Tom
MacArthur
of New Jersey is now a yes.

04:37.244 --> 04:38.979 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

04:39.012 --> 04:40.780 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TOM MACARTHUR (R), New Jersey:
The speaker,
the majority leader of the
Senate and the

04:40.814 --> 04:45.352 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
president have all agreed that
they would
publicly make it clear that's
the only purpose

04:45.385 --> 04:50.557 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for which they will support the
use of the
$85 billion that we put into the
bill.

04:50.590 --> 04:52.259 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But it's close.

04:52.292 --> 04:54.194 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Freshman Dan Donovan is still
thinking.

04:54.227 --> 04:55.262 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

04:55.295 --> 04:57.164 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAN DONOVAN (R), New York: I'm
not saying
yet.

04:57.197 --> 05:00.600 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: It's close
enough that GOP
leaders are looking for votes
from small groups,

05:00.634 --> 05:03.336 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
