05:11.444 --> 05:13.113 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Representative Chris Collins
pushed the idea.

05:13.146 --> 05:14.881 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

05:14.915 --> 05:18.418 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHRIS COLLINS (R), New York: It
shifts the
burden from the local taxpayer
back to the

05:18.451 --> 05:22.189 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
state government, which is how
it's handled
in every other state in the
nation.

05:22.222 --> 05:24.357 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But New York
Democrat Joe
Crowley balked.

05:24.391 --> 05:26.226 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

05:26.259 --> 05:28.595 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOE CROWLEY (D), New York: This
will significantly
hurt individuals in New York who
could face

05:28.628 --> 05:34.201 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
