those in their
districts by bring down
premiums, offering

08:10.590 --> 08:12.425 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
more choices.

08:12.459 --> 08:15.028 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's the kind of core Republican
arguments
we have seen, but they have got
to stare straight

08:15.061 --> 08:19.899 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in the face of many of these
moderates who
have heavy Medicaid populations,
lots of folks

08:19.933 --> 08:22.268 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on Medicaid, and they are
concerned about
what will happen to them.

08:22.302 --> 08:23.703 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I talked to Charlie Dent.

08:23.737 --> 08:26.773 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He is one of those moderate
members concerned
about Medicaid.

08:26.806 --> 08:28.508 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He walked out of that White
House office.

08:28.541 --> 08:29.976 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I spoke to him.

08:30.009 --> 08:32.879 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he said he still has the
same reservations
that he had going in.

08:32.912 --> 08:37.050 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, Lisa,
finally, if they
are able to get it through the
House, what

08:37.083 --> 08:39.119 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
