38:49.160 --> 38:52.997 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
William Brangham recently
visited there, and
he is back again with this
report.

38:53.031 --> 38:55.934 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's part of our weekly series
Making the
Grade.

38:55.967 --> 39:01.039 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Fish swim in
giant tanks.

39:01.072 --> 39:04.375 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Collard greens grow in abundance
in a massive
greenhouse.

39:04.409 --> 39:08.479 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Down the hall, there's a
dentist's office,
as well as a mental health
center.

39:08.513 --> 39:15.486 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And at the other end of the
building, 3-,
4-, and 5-year-olds run around
like mad.

39:15.520 --> 39:21.726 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Some might say it's an unusual
mix here in
the heart of one of Denver's
poorest neighborhoods,

39:21.759 --> 39:23.661 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but not according to the woman
who runs the
place.

39:23.695 --> 39:25.430 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

39:25.463 --> 39:25.997 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LYDIA PRADO, Dahlia Campus for
Health and
Well-Being: It's taking a new
approach to

39:26.030 --> 39:27.498 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
community well-being.

39:27.532 --> 39:29.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Dr. Lydia
Prado is the driving
force behind this place.

39:29.901 --> 39:32.470 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's called the Dahlia Campus
for Health and
Well-Being.

39:32.503 --> 39:34.305 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

39:34.339 --> 39:36.541 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LYDIA PRADO: My initial
conversations were
with two folks who had --
together, they have

39:36.574 --> 39:39.844 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
over 80 years of residence in
this community.

39:39.877 --> 39:43.615 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And just floated the idea, I
want to take
integrated care to the next
level.

39:43.648 --> 39:46.184 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I want to think comprehensively
about health.

39:46.217 --> 39:49.587 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I want to be able to talk about
mental health,
and went to talk to them about
it, and it's

39:49.621 --> 39:51.055 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
like, what do you think?

39:51.089 --> 39:52.156 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And they're like, oh.

39:52.190 --> 39:54.092 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, you know, they were very
honest about
it.

39:54.125 --> 39:58.029 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
There are going to be
challenges, but if anybody's
going to give it a shot -- and
we're behind

39:58.062 --> 39:59.497 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
you.

39:59.530 --> 40:02.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: For Prado,
building partnerships
early on was key.

40:02.634 --> 40:08.072 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Heidi Heissenbuttel came on
board early, bringing
a branch of her Sewall Child
Development Center

40:08.106 --> 40:09.874 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to the new campus.

40:09.907 --> 40:14.612 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Sewall's been a pioneer in
what's known as
inclusive education, teaching
children with

40:14.646 --> 40:19.384 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
special needs -- that is, kids
with autism
or those with emotional or
behavioral issues

40:19.417 --> 40:24.656 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
-- and putting them in
classrooms with their
more typically developing peers.

40:24.689 --> 40:29.093 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Heissenbuttel says the evidence
is clear that
this approach works for all
kids.

40:29.127 --> 40:32.397 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HEIDI HEISSENBUTTEL, Sewall
Child Development
Center: They learn to expect
that every child

40:32.430 --> 40:37.302 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
learns differently, and they go
on to their
elementary classrooms, and they
become advocates

40:37.335 --> 40:39.103 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
for kids who learn differently.

40:39.137 --> 40:44.042 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And they will tell teachers, you
need to work
with that child, or why can't he
participate

40:44.075 --> 40:46.944 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on the playground, or we want
him in our group.

40:46.978 --> 40:50.248 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: We observed
three classrooms.

40:50.281 --> 40:53.184 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Here, the Tigers have circle
time.

40:53.217 --> 40:58.556 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then they moved on to center
time, an hour
when the children get to pick
what they want

40:58.589 --> 41:04.395 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to do, as teachers float through
the classroom
facilitating vocabulary-building
and individual

41:04.429 --> 41:06.397 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
lessons.

41:06.431 --> 41:11.669 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One-third of the children here
have some special
need, some with diagnosed
developmental problems.

41:11.703 --> 41:16.607 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Plus, 40 percent of the kids
here suffer from
what's known as toxic stress.

41:16.641 --> 41:24.082 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HEIDI HEISSENBUTTEL: Toxic
stress is the result
of poverty, abuse and neglect,
domestic violence,

41:24.115 --> 41:30.355 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
just life's circumstances, when
you -- when
a family lives under stress.

41:30.388 --> 41:35.360 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And what the best treatment, for
children
to have loving, stable
relationships in their

41:35.393 --> 41:37.095 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
lives.

41:37.128 --> 41:40.298 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Arnesha Poke's
son Adrian
(ph) attends the pre-K, and she
says this

41:40.331 --> 41:43.034 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
inclusive approach is important
to her.

41:43.067 --> 41:47.305 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ARNESHA POKE, Mother: Instead
of, like, separating
the kids off and stuff, they
need to all be

41:47.338 --> 41:52.377 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
together, so they can learn each
other and
learn each other's emotional
ways, and stuff

41:52.410 --> 41:53.378 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
like that.

41:53.411 --> 41:55.346 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

41:55.380 --> 41:59.450 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LYDIA PRADO: In the community
conversation,
it was extremely important, this
idea of inclusivity,

41:59.484 --> 42:07.258 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
because it was -- it's parallel
to a community's
desire to be included and
inclusive.

42:07.291 --> 42:09.961 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's a lot of experience of
being separated
out.

42:09.994 --> 42:14.031 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DIANE GREENBERG, Mother: I
thought she would
kind of fall in with the rest of
the kids

42:14.065 --> 42:18.636 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and just do -- not have any
problems, issues
at all.

42:18.669 --> 42:22.306 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Diane
Greenberg and her
daughter Karai (ph) used to live
in a homeless

42:22.340 --> 42:23.307 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
shelter.

42:23.341 --> 42:25.410 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She says this preschool has been
life-changing.

42:25.443 --> 42:32.250 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DIANE GREENBERG: I love this
place because
it helps me understand how to
deal with that.

42:32.283 --> 42:34.485 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It helps me understand how to
help her.

42:34.519 --> 42:39.490 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The
staff-to-child ratio
here is one to five, whereas the
state only

42:39.524 --> 42:41.392 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
mandates a 1-10 ratio.

42:41.426 --> 42:45.263 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TRINA POKE, Teacher: I think we
all respect
each other and we all do like
each other enough.

42:45.296 --> 42:47.231 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Teachers Trina
Poke and
Christine Krall.

42:47.265 --> 42:51.969 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TRINA POKE: We just kind of get
so used to
each other that we do just tend
to feed off

42:52.003 --> 42:53.771 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of each other like that.

42:53.805 --> 42:56.507 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHRISTINE KRALL, Teacher: I
especially feel
sometimes that it's not easy to
see what I'm

42:56.541 --> 42:58.409 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
doing.

42:58.443 --> 43:01.746 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's when I will share,
like, the rationale
and things like that during team
meetings,

43:01.779 --> 43:06.684 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
so it doesn't look like I'm just
playing,
because there is a method to the
madness.

43:06.717 --> 43:11.189 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Some of the
madness is designed
to calm children down who may be
having a

43:11.222 --> 43:12.523 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
tough time.

43:12.557 --> 43:14.258 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Heather Luehers is a social
worker.

43:14.292 --> 43:16.961 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HEATHER LUEHERS, Social Worker:
When kids
can't pay attention to parents,
when they

43:16.994 --> 43:24.168 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are so dysregulated, they have
problems, because
they move inside themselves, and
they just

43:24.202 --> 43:25.369 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
run around the classroom.

43:25.403 --> 43:27.705 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think, in some of our
classrooms, you
see that.

43:27.738 --> 43:33.611 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, what I'm doing with this
child is saying,
I'm the adult, I'm in charge,
you don't need

43:33.644 --> 43:38.149 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
